Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.63,0:01:09.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bullying?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.14,0:01:10.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And really stereotypical stuff, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.79,0:01:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turning right!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.13,0:01:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now then, let's have a chat about those human\Nexperiments you're involved with.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.76,0:01:19.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.26,0:01:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.54,0:01:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They know where I was heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.89,0:01:25.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've found you, my love!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.52,0:01:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need any excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.85,0:01:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or would you rather be\Nthe material yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.83,0:01:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.75,0:01:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you don't need a head.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.20,0:01:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's always the important\Nstuff you lose, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.48,0:02:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like a brand new umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.63,0:02:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You never lose your crappy old one.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.40,0:02:07.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind losing an umbrella,\Nbut a winning lottery ticket...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.61,0:02:10.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You put them somewhere important\Nbut then forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.58,0:02:14.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you look for them,\Nyou end up finding all these other things.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.01,0:02:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we just think the things we lose are\Nmore important than we would otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.91,0:02:19.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.17,0:02:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looking for something?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.31,0:02:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I think...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.05,0:02:32.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm asleep, maybe I'm awake there.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.77,0:02:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sometimes, I feel that since\Nmy memories got hazy,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.17,0:02:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my sense of passing time\Nhas gotten hazy, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.79,0:02:43.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long has it been?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.08,0:02:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since I stopped seeing myself\Nwhole, even in dreams?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.45,0:02:54.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here and there...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.70,0:02:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the there, but not here,\Nwhat types of things do I see?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.01,0:03:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the dream I have over and over,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.61,0:03:10.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I try to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:21.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But the dream's always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.84,0:03:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Celty!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.59,0:04:00.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.13,0:04:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Last night, you said you didn't\Nhave work today, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.60,0:04:09.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just did the calculations.\NIt's your first day off in 265 days!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.84,0:04:15.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The look on your face is unhappy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.25,0:04:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He reads expressions on\Nthe face I don't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.32,0:04:28.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that humans have dreams in order\Nto organize their memories. Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.28,0:04:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's certainly a sudden question.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.39,0:04:33.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do people dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.62,0:04:37.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Put simply: no one knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.48,0:04:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Medicine has a long way\Nto go in lots of areas,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.56,0:04:42.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,especially concerning what\Nhappens up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.59,0:04:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone knows that you have dreams\Nduring REM, rapid eye movement...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.82,0:04:49.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.32,0:04:51.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An underground doctor, to be precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.66,0:04:55.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But to be honest, I don't really\Nknow what he does.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.82,0:05:03.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's letting me live here, and it's thanks to him\Nthat I can continue my job as a transporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.53,0:05:08.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess the issue is that no one\Nreally knows what "memories" are.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.79,0:05:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You listening?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.27,0:05:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel grateful for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.33,0:05:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And lately, I've thought that what\NI feel for him is probably love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.62,0:05:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.95,0:05:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to think your memories are\Nin your head, but we don't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.59,0:05:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.71,0:05:34.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, first let's change.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.91,0:05:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can go somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.19,0:05:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take the day off, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.31,0:05:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See? I'll turn off the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.08,0:05:47.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pull the interweb feed too!\NI won't check my emails at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.93,0:05:50.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The whole day is ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.80,0:05:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where shall we go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.97,0:05:55.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take your horse to the sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.24,0:05:56.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or a hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.43,0:05:58.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.17,0:06:00.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.66,0:06:05.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we're taking the day off, I'd like to cook for you, thanking you for all you've done for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.46,0:06:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Home cooking!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.80,0:06:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.44,0:06:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for a recipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.42,0:06:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so moved, Celty!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.06,0:06:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what I'd like...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.93,0:06:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK, thanks so much, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.66,0:06:31.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I overslept this morning, so it really helps.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.23,0:06:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem, young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.21,0:06:36.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured you'd eventually get\Ntired from the trip to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.29,0:06:40.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Times like this are your hunter chance!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoulder to shoulder with the lovely\Nlady next to you, sharing textbooks!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.03,0:06:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what's up? You going\Nwithout the necktie?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.91,0:06:49.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or did you just forget?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.11,0:06:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.61,0:06:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't forget your wallet, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.89,0:06:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.44,0:07:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's yummy!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Russian sushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.69,0:07:13.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simon, you seen Yumacchi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.97,0:07:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Karisawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.66,0:07:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want sushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.87,0:07:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have not seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.16,0:07:20.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No luck, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.26,0:07:20.64,Default - Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,Big trouble today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.63,0:07:22.78,Default - Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,The owner got sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.19,0:07:24.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dengeki Bunko's {\i1}accel World{\i0} comes out today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.02,0:07:25.69,Default - Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,But he is OK now!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.88,0:07:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The two of us went to buy it,\Nthen got some tea and split up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.69,0:07:27.75,Default - Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,He took medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.75,0:07:30.00,Default - Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,But he could not go to get fish.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.64,0:07:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But one of the café maids came after me,\Nsaying Yumacchi forgot his cell.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.00,0:07:31.93,Default - Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,So we have no ingredients.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.93,0:07:34.07,Default - Alt,,0000,0000,0000,,We are looking for them now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.03,0:07:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.92,0:07:36.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't attract customers then!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.86,0:07:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.74,0:07:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.97,0:07:40.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.04,0:07:41.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said it's Yumacchi's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.61,0:07:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.70,0:07:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lost objects?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.36,0:07:50.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Write what you're looking for here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.16,0:07:51.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.72,0:07:57.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you doing this all day?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.01,0:07:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am asking everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.36,0:08:06.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.71,0:08:09.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.66,0:08:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I looking for?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:20.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's enough that Kazutawno's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.14,0:08:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I promised Karisawa and Yumasaki\NI'd stop looking into this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.65,0:08:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yagiri Pharmaceuticals...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.91,0:08:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They say they're secretly hooked up with the Awakusu
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.46,0:08:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or the North American Nebra, Inc.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.37,0:08:41.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm not gonna find anything by standing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.31,0:09:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you see Karisawa?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.40,0:09:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have not.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.05,0:09:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.92,0:09:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, how about some Russian sushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.75,0:09:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Celty! Let's use a kitchen knife, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.80,0:09:35.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.55,0:09:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.68,0:09:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.60,0:09:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait. Why are you crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.05,0:09:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.74,0:09:47.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.85,0:09:49.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's truly wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.80,0:09:51.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These super-sweet sautéed and\Nsimmered veggies,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.87,0:09:53.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the bitterness of the miso soup...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.71,0:09:55.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.38,0:09:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. Your cooking is avant-garde!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.45,0:09:59.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.12,0:10:03.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not a compliment!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.17,0:10:06.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it. I screwed it up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.35,0:10:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.21,0:10:08.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't force yourself to eat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.68,0:10:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not forcing myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.43,0:10:12.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's so good...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.61,0:10:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I said, "Don't eat it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.17,0:10:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.89,0:10:30.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How's this thing work, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.29,0:10:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, you've got a talent\Nfor cooking. I know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.42,0:10:38.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who cares if you don't have "watermelon cells"?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.10,0:10:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Watermelons?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.39,0:10:44.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean a sense of taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.11,0:10:48.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The brain doesn't have tastes that\Naren't recorded in your DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.49,0:10:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But you don't have to eat, and it looks like\Nthe brain has nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.99,0:10:58.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.71,0:11:00.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Want to play a game?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.90,0:11:03.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't treat me like a kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.96,0:11:06.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That pisses me off more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.03,0:11:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.55,0:11:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You do teach me a lot of things,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.71,0:11:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but some of the hazy memories I have\Ndate back a hundred years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.38,0:11:17.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my head has more...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.20,0:11:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you need memories from\Nhundreds of years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.31,0:11:23.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.11,0:11:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's like I'm always saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.81,0:11:29.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're fine the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.89,0:11:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.87,0:11:37.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like I'm going to\Nforget my own face!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.93,0:11:43.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.38,0:11:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Celty!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.03,0:11:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.86,0:12:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You need to keep your phone on, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.43,0:12:06.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a patient in a critical condition, and we couldn't reach you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.20,0:12:23.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonohara, is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.90,0:12:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.72,0:12:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.00,0:12:28.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you lose this time, Mikado?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.93,0:12:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonohara's shoes are gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.16,0:12:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.44,0:12:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, people need to get a life.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.96,0:12:38.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got a good idea who's doing this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.39,0:12:39.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kida...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.58,0:12:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.46,0:12:42.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Kida!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.38,0:12:51.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kida was kinda scary.\NHe's not normally like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.34,0:12:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.68,0:12:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He ran off. That guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.11,0:13:16.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I was a kid, I used to\Nlose things all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.28,0:13:20.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'd always cry, "I can't\Nfind it! I can't find it!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.12,0:13:23.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And my mom would help me look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.76,0:13:25.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your mom's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.14,0:13:27.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.33,0:13:29.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My mom and dad both.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.61,0:13:35.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.35,0:13:39.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.13,0:13:43.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Ryuugamine,\Nfor looking with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.43,0:13:52.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give up on whoever it is, Kida.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.44,0:13:56.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No. She went home.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.25,0:13:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.53,0:14:01.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.73,0:14:04.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still looking, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.72,0:14:07.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, see you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.49,0:14:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There they are!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.39,0:14:25.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.64,0:14:31.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:35.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't remember at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.81,0:14:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Empty lots are weird, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.26,0:14:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once everything's gone, you can't\Nremember what was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.51,0:14:44.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Used to be something here, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.78,0:14:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something pretty big.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.59,0:14:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:58.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get mad when Shinra tells me\Nto stop looking for my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:15:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But doing a job, making friends...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.65,0:15:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it like I think I'm human?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.55,0:15:11.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you want to talk to\Nme about something?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.63,0:15:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.07,0:15:22.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a long, thin, blue building, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:27.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that old, crappy one!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.03,0:15:29.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was an elderly lady who sold\Ncigarettes on the first floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.45,0:15:31.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice work, transporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.58,0:15:38.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure I can sense\Nmy head in this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.30,0:15:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, how are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.44,0:15:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.12,0:15:57.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am searching for beautiful Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.84,0:16:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me what it is you are\Nlooking for in your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.56,0:16:08.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Can I see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.66,0:16:09.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,OK!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if she met him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.77,0:16:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I looked for a lot of things today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.95,0:16:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I found some, and I didn't find some.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.61,0:17:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His bag was gone, so I thought\Nhe was at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.65,0:17:02.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.55,0:17:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something felt unusual.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.70,0:17:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.96,0:17:18.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. They were going nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.46,0:17:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It took several people to put him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.47,0:17:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All for fireworks?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.59,0:17:26.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, your staff is harsh.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.38,0:17:29.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It causes problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.72,0:17:31.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was talking nonsense.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.54,0:17:33.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Said his girlfriend was kidnapped,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.27,0:17:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and she could only remember this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.19,0:17:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Demanded to know what we did to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.67,0:17:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not nonsense. It's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.87,0:17:45.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you make it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.61,0:17:51.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so he won't remember anything about us\Nwhen he wakes up, Doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.26,0:17:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no easy way to erase\Nmemories like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.35,0:17:59.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I'll remember this kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.63,0:18:01.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll send him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.56,0:18:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno whether to his\Nhouse or not, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.96,0:18:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor... The chief and\NI, we both trust you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.01,0:18:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're keeping our big secret, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.73,0:18:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. You're living with quite\Na strange houseguest, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.03,0:18:28.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.69,0:18:31.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had forgotten...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.01,0:18:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About my head...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.54,0:18:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the memories of hundreds of years\Nof being a Dullahan inside it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.53,0:18:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't thinking of anything,\Njust... just...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.84,0:19:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, would you come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.11,0:19:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I ask for two plates,\Nthe restaurant won't complain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.60,0:19:10.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know a good place.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.26,0:19:11.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, Celty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.36,0:19:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't like eating alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.00,0:19:20.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this bizarre dish?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.19,0:19:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fried chicken sushi, cheese sushi, mabo\Nsushi, prosciutto sushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.97,0:19:33.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and this is sour cream sushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.70,0:19:35.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Those things shouldn't be\Nmade into sushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.54,0:19:36.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.74,0:19:38.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a special set!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.10,0:19:39.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a great deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.24,0:19:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And a fortune cookie for dessert? Sheesh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.51,0:19:51.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's got a fortune inside, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:53.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.67,0:19:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.71,0:20:03.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.72,0:20:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This means you'll find what\Nyou're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.27,0:20:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know if I like you\Nquite that happy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.98,0:20:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so happy, Shinra!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.28,0:20:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.52,0:20:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.72,0:20:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.15,0:20:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I'm sad here,\Ndoes my head weep there?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.60,0:21:05.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.54,0:21:12.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope not.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.70,0:21:19.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope it's smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.45,0:21:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.21,0:21:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.38,0:21:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.85,0:21:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.44,0:21:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can remember anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.73,0:21:42.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.51,0:21:44.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.01,0:21:46.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your past or your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.30,0:21:49.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just you, as you are now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.60,0:21:52.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I, right now, are eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.76,0:21:58.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I love you, Celty.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.35,0:22:18.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That night, for the first time in a long while,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.09,0:22:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had a dream of when I was whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.67,0:24:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0010,,My love is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.59,0:24:20.76,Default,,0000,0000,0010,,It isn't like the love that only seeks and asks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.25,0:24:23.30,Default,,0000,0000,0010,,It's a more perfect thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.83,0:24:24.78,Default,,0000,0000,0010,,Next time:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.78,0:24:26.00,Default,,0000,0000,0010,,Love and Cherish.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.00,0:24:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0010,,I'm what Seiji needs.
